.TH MYSHELL "1" "December 2025" "myshell 202208141225-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
myshell \- Change the default user shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B myshell
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,SHELL\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B myshell
is a utility script for changing the default login shell for the current user. It provides an interactive menu to select from available shells installed on the system.
.PP
The script simplifies the process of changing shells by presenting available options and handling the chsh command.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " " \fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR
Set the working directory
.TP
.BR \-\-term
Open the shell selector in a terminal window
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B myshell
Launch interactive shell selection menu
.TP
.B myshell /bin/zsh
Change default shell to zsh
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/myshell/settings.conf
User configuration file for myshell preferences
.TP
.B /etc/shells
List of valid login shells
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or shell change failed
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Opens in a terminal if not already running in one
.IP \(bu 2
Lists shells from /etc/shells
.IP \(bu 2
May require password for shell change
